==English==

===Etymology===
Borrowed from {{bor|en|fr|massicot}}; English {{m|en|masticot}} is a corruption.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# {{lb|en|chemistry}} [[lead monoxide]], PbO, obtained as a yellow amorphous powder, the fused and crystalline form of which is called [[litharge]]; [[lead ocher]]. It is used as a pigment; also, ''lead oxide yellow'', as opposed to [[red lead]], which is [[lead tetroxide]] Pb<sub>3</sub>O<sub>4</sub>.
#: '''Note''' Massicot is sometimes used by painters, and also as a drier in the composition of ointments and plasters.
#: '''Quotations'''
#:* '''1952''': Besides orpiment, already referred to, one occasionally gets mention of '''massicot''', a yellow lead paint. &mdash; L.F. Salzman, ''Building in England'', p. 169.

